		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30707207">One thing interesting about the Haruhi LNs is just how influential its setup is. No light novel clone (or adaptation of it) can get the Haruhi formula quite right. It's an ordinary life with a touch of the extraordinary—sure, most derivatives can get that right—but the close encounters, easily accessible but relatable script, and the engaging character relationships set the bar really high.<br />
<br />
I actually believe Kyon's monologues feel much more authentic in the anime, whereas in the light novel, sparse descriptions of things like the setting make it difficult to immerse oneself into the world. It's typical of light novels I guess.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
