		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30715175">I am making no judgement on the LN here, as I haven't read it. I think a list of light novels with sales sorted per year would be useful in determining whether that influential setup really is Haruhi's as I lack knowledge in the demographic, as do most Western fans (I think) due to the low volume of available material. Whatever LNs or group of LNs it is that introduced the setup, though, it could be partly to be blamed for generating all the soulless wish-fulfilment kid prose that followed and made its way into the anime medium. <br />
<br />
@Kuiper: If you ever find the time to, I think you would be providing some of the most interesting analysis in the club so far if you took some specific examples of scenes that were better in the novel for the reasons you suggested and pasted the raw text alongside subbed screenshots from the anime so that we can know exactly what you mean. I know this kind of stuff's time-consuming though.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
