		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30716001">I don't have the time either, although it wouldn't be difficult to grab annual top sales rankings and subset to the "soulless wish-fulfilment kid prose" ones. Props to anyone else who wants to do it! I think it's safe to say however that while Haruhi may not have invented the style (I'm honestly not sure), Haruhi codified it, in the same way Rose of Versailles is not the first shoujo but it's one of the earliest examples whose influence established the standard for the demographic/genre.<br />
<br />
On "blame": Sure, if on the same slant LOGH could be partly to be blamed for generating few alike stories to follow, because investors saw the weak profit in LOGH. Personally, I'd do the safer thing and not do such fingerpointing. :)</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
