		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30716389">I would not do any such fingerpointing either, but here's the thing: I think when some people feel inclined to 'celebrate an anime for introducing many people to the medium' or 'respect a work for the influence it has', they have to acknowledge points that go in the opposite direction.<br />
<br />
I personally neither go for such praise nor criticism, but since you brought up the matter of influence (in a fairly neutral way) it felt appropriate to say that, in this case as in many, I don't think influence is necessarily positive or even praiseworthy considering the gears of the industry.<br />
<br />
(As for your example- for the record, IMO introducing a formula that works is significantly different from introducing one that doesn't, as works that fit into the latter case would not make any historical difference)</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
