		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30824191">Perhaps I'm a bit biased here, having watched the anime first, but for me the dialogue in the light novel doesn't have quite the same impact as the anime opening. Though you can pick up the tone from the words on the page, it doesn't carry the same impact as when Crispin Freeman delivered those lines, as you could pick up a stronger sense of general resignment/longing/whatever etc. In this way I felt I learned more about kyon through the spoken dialogue, though that again may just be confirmation bias combined with a good english voiceacting performance.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
